1
00:01:21,430 --> 00:01:26,990
[Brocade Odyssey]

2
00:01:27,210 --> 00:01:29,810
[Episode 25]

3
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:23,830
Mr. Yang, Ms. Ji, it's time to wake up.

4
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,240
All right. Please don't come in now.

5
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:29,190
Wait a moment!

6
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,440
Don't come in!

7
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:42,000
Without our permission,

8
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:43,880
they won't be allowed in.

9
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,320
Come in.

10
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,080
I am Jinxiu, your servant.

11
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:56,240
Greetings to Mr. Yang and Ms. Ji.

12
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,030
Madam told me

13
00:02:58,030 --> 00:02:59,830
to bring these maids

14
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,630
to serve in your place.

15
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:04,320
We await your orders, Mr. Yang and Ms. Ji.

16
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:12,440
Yingying.

17
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:14,440
Yingying.

18
00:03:21,270 --> 00:03:22,080
Rise.

19
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:23,030
Thank you, Mr. Yang,

20
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:23,880
and Ms. Ji.

21
00:04:11,670 --> 00:04:12,960
Our Yang family has many strict rules.

22
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,470
It may take some time for you to adapt.

23
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,480
But don't worry.

24
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:18,790
As long as I'm here,

25
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:20,880
no one will dare to bully you.

26
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:23,880
For now,

27
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:26,720
the most important thing is to rescue your mother.

28
00:04:28,790 --> 00:04:30,760
Thank you, Yang Jinglan.

29
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,200
No need to thank me.

30
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,550
We have plenty of time ahead.

31
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:49,760
Look at all this blood.

32
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,390
It's soaked into the planks.

33
00:04:51,790 --> 00:04:53,600
If I don't replace them,

34
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,480
no one will dare to take my boat.

35
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:57,230
Such bad luck!

36
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,000
Enough, stop complaining.

37
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,670
Is that enough to replace the planks?

38
00:05:10,790 --> 00:05:11,670
It's more than enough!

39
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,830
Could you tell us exactly

40
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:15,350
what happened that day?

41
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,670
A man should build a family and career,

42
00:05:18,670 --> 00:05:20,200
but where's your career now?

43
00:05:20,350 --> 00:05:21,110
You're a grown man.

44
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:22,510
Don't you feel any shame?

45
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,350
Boatman,

46
00:05:28,550 --> 00:05:29,480
when will we dock?

47
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:30,550
Soon.

48
00:05:30,950 --> 00:05:32,110
Why don't you stay in the cabin

49
00:05:32,110 --> 00:05:33,390
and rest a little longer?

50
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,270
Those two women are too noisy.

51
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:37,320
I came out for some fresh air.

52
00:05:43,790 --> 00:05:44,670
We're almost there.

53
00:05:44,670 --> 00:05:45,760
I'll go check on them.

54
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,000
Murder! Murder!

55
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:58,200
She killed my wife!

56
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,350
Quick, report to the authorities!

57
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,640
So you didn't

58
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:02,350
see my mother kill her with your own eyes?

59
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:04,830
What does it matter if I saw it personally or not?

60
00:06:05,670 --> 00:06:07,760
There were only two people in the cabin.

61
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,200
If your mother hadn't killed her,

62
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,040
who else could have done it? A ghost?

63
00:06:43,790 --> 00:06:45,440
Do you usually light incense on your boat?

64
00:06:45,830 --> 00:06:46,760
Yes.

65
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:48,390
It keeps mosquitoes away.

66
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:50,600
But that's strange

67
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:53,000
because since they boarded my boat,

68
00:06:53,350 --> 00:06:55,070
the incense burner has disappeared.

69
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:57,000
It's truly odd.

70
00:06:58,380 --> 00:07:01,010
[Case Report]

71
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:04,160
The wound on her neck

72
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,200
is the only fatal wound.

73
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,550
This is the murder weapon.

74
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:14,200
It is indeed my mother's hairpin.

75
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,000
And over here.

76
00:07:17,390 --> 00:07:19,200
These outer garments belong to your mother,

77
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:20,950
your aunt, and Li Feng.

78
00:07:25,230 --> 00:07:26,480
They're stored as evidence

79
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:29,230
because of the bloodstains.

80
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,440
Do you notice anything unusual?

81
00:08:06,830 --> 00:08:08,440
The stains on these two garments aren't blood.

82
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,760
They're dye.

83
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,790
Dye?

84
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,830
I know what was going on now.

85
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:21,880
This case is actually very simple.

86
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,230
It's just that the county magistrate refuses to investigate.

87
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,320
The victim's husband, Li Feng,

88
00:08:32,670 --> 00:08:35,440
and the boatman, Yu San, both testified

89
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,030
that on the day of the incident,

90
00:08:37,110 --> 00:08:40,200
Mrs. Li and Mrs. Ji argued on the boat.

91
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,550
As the boat was about to dock,

92
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,400
the two men entered the cabin

93
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:45,790
and found the victim

94
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:48,230
stabbed to death with a hairpin by Mrs. Ji.

95
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:50,400
The evidence and testimony are conclusive.

96
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,670
Ms. Ji,

97
00:08:52,590 --> 00:08:54,440
on what grounds do you claim your mother was wronged?

98
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,790
Speak truthfully to this court.

99
00:08:57,230 --> 00:08:58,590
I have three points of doubt, Your Honor.

100
00:08:58,880 --> 00:08:59,790
First,

101
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,400
according to the boatman Yu San's testimony,

102
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,880
he did not see my mother committing murder personally.

103
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:07,400
Instead, he heard shouting after Li Feng

104
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,790
entered the cabin.

105
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,670
Then,

106
00:09:09,670 --> 00:09:11,520
he saw my aunt covered in blood,

107
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,790
lying in Li Feng's arms.

108
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:14,670
Blocked by Li Feng,

109
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,000
he might not have even seen

110
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,030
if my aunt had any wounds.

111
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,000
The boat was in the middle of the river,

112
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
surrounded by no one.

113
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:22,640
In that cabin, it was only your mother and your aunt.

114
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:23,790
If your mother hadn't killed her,

115
00:09:23,790 --> 00:09:24,760
then who else could have done it?

116
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,080
Why don't we suspect

117
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,790
the first person who found the victim?

118
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:30,840
Li Feng and the boatman entered the cabin one after the other,

119
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,400
only moments apart.

120
00:09:32,670 --> 00:09:34,150
How could he have had time to kill?

121
00:09:34,590 --> 00:09:36,880
And why didn't the two women resist

122
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,150
or make any noise?

123
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,790
That's my second point of doubt.

124
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:44,000
If my mother was the murderer,

125
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:46,760
then why was she also found unconscious on the boat?

126
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:48,880
Perhaps your mother hit her head

127
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,200
while committing the murder

128
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:51,670
and fainted.

129
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:54,030
Or she was overcome by fear after the act

130
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:56,080
and passed out.

131
00:09:56,350 --> 00:09:57,760
Those are possible scenarios,

132
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,440
but there's another explanation.

133
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:02,590
My mother was framed.

134
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,400
Both she and my aunt were drugged unconscious.

135
00:10:05,590 --> 00:10:07,470
Your claims are mere speculation,

136
00:10:08,590 --> 00:10:09,840
unsupported by evidence.

137
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,670
I have proof, Your Honor.

138
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:14,550
Please examine it.

139
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:23,880
Here is the incense ash that I found

140
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:25,000
on Yu San's boat.

141
00:10:25,230 --> 00:10:27,000
I had it examined by a physician.

142
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,840
It contains datura

143
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,550
and other sleep-promoting herbs.

144
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:32,400
If Your Honor don't believe me,

145
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,440
you may have another physician verify it.

146
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:37,400
You say you found it on the boat.

147
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,760
How can you prove it was from the boat?

148
00:10:40,350 --> 00:10:41,200
Mr. Zhuge!

149
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:42,590
Please make way.

150
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:50,790
Your Honor,

151
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:53,000
Inspector Yang is unwell

152
00:10:53,150 --> 00:10:55,110
and has tasked me and the Qianniu Guards

153
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:57,000
with assisting Ms. Ji in this case.

154
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:59,000
I can testify

155
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,230
that this incense ash

156
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,400
was indeed discovered on Yu San's boat.

157
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,840
This matter is unrelated to the brocade industry,

158
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,400
so there's no need for Inspector Yang to be troubled.

159
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:08,440
Your Honor, that's not accurate.

160
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,280
The one suffering from this case

161
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:12,030
is the president of the Bloom Society.

162
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:13,880
How could it be unrelated to brocade affairs?

163
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,400
Still, Inspector Yang trusts

164
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,790
that you will uncover the truth,

165
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:19,790
and has no intention of interfering.

166
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:21,150
However, the murderer

167
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:22,400
committed the crime openly,

168
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,590
showing great nerve.

169
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:26,200
Surely, someone must be behind this.

170
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:28,670
Inspector Yang sent me here

171
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:30,880
to remind Ms. Ji

172
00:11:31,350 --> 00:11:32,880
that you also have allies on your back.

173
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,280
There's no need to fear them.

174
00:11:37,350 --> 00:11:39,150
So what if it was found on the boat?

175
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:40,150
How can you prove

176
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:41,640
that it was the incense lit by the boatman on that day

177
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,400
and that your mother

178
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:44,550
was drugged by it?

179
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:46,350
That's right.

180
00:11:46,910 --> 00:11:47,910
How can you prove it?

181
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:49,590
I can't prove it.

182
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:50,840
If you can't prove it,

183
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:51,840
why bring it up at all?

184
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:56,080
Nevertheless, I have a third point of doubt.

185
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,440
I ask Your Honor to allow me to present it.

186
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,400
If I don't allow you to continue,

187
00:11:58,400 --> 00:11:59,350
will you really stop?

188
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,350
These three outer garments

189
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:05,200
belong to my mother, my aunt, and Li Feng who were wearing them respectively

190
00:12:05,350 --> 00:12:07,000
on the day of the incident.

191
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,520
Your Honor, take a look.

192
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:11,150
Do you notice any difference in the bloodstains?

193
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,200
What difference could there be?

194
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,230
I won't look at them.

195
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,000
Fine.

196
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:17,230
Then let everyone else take a look.

197
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:20,110
What's the difference in the bloodstains on these garments?

198
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:32,080
Why is the color on this one

199
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,590
different from the others?

200
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:35,400
Even the smell is not the same.

201
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,790
The bloodstain on Mrs. Ji's garment

202
00:12:37,790 --> 00:12:39,000
has a noticeably fainter smell.

203
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,590
Because some of it is blood,

204
00:12:41,790 --> 00:12:43,760
and some of it is dye.

205
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:48,470
Most of the stains

206
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:50,470
on my mother's garment are dyes.

207
00:12:50,550 --> 00:12:52,230
Your family runs a dyehouse.

208
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:54,030
It's not strange for your mother's garment

209
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:55,760
to have dye on it.

210
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:57,200
But my aunt does not work in a dyehouse.

211
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,350
Why does her garment also have dye?

212
00:13:00,230 --> 00:13:01,670
And why does Li Feng's garment

213
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:04,000
have only blood

214
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,200
and no dye at all?

215
00:13:05,230 --> 00:13:06,000
Ji Yingying,

216
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,400
even if your three points of doubt

217
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,150
are true,

218
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:12,590
they have nothing to do with the truth of this case.

219
00:13:12,590 --> 00:13:13,590
Of course they do.

220
00:13:14,470 --> 00:13:15,960
These three points, when connected,

221
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,670
can prove

222
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:18,790
that my mother is not the murderer.

223
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,710
The true murderer

224
00:13:20,710 --> 00:13:21,670
is him,

225
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:22,670
Li Feng!

226
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:24,000
Utter nonsense!

227
00:13:26,420 --> 00:13:26,590
IOU?

228
00:13:26,590 --> 00:13:27,280
From the very beginning,

229
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:29,080
Li Feng planned this entire scheme.

230
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,910
The argument in the cabin that day

231
00:13:30,910 --> 00:13:32,640
was not between my mother and my aunt.

232
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,400
It was Li Feng deliberately causing a scene

233
00:13:34,910 --> 00:13:36,520
to make the boatman hear arguments.

234
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:38,230
At the same time, he lit an incense stick

235
00:13:38,230 --> 00:13:39,520
in the cabin's corner.

236
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:40,790
Then, he left under some excuse.

237
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,670
Shortly after Li Feng left,

238
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:43,790
my mother and aunt

239
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:44,910
both fell unconscious.

240
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:46,790
Outside the cabin,

241
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:48,150
Li Feng deliberately engaged Yu San in conversation.

242
00:13:48,540 --> 00:13:48,880
Soon.

243
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:51,440
He told Yu San that it was

244
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:53,470
my mother and aunt who were arguing in the cabin,

245
00:13:53,470 --> 00:13:55,280
creating a motive for my mother to commit murder.

246
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,840
When the boat was about to dock,

247
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,550
he acted concerned and entered the cabin to call for them.

248
00:14:00,830 --> 00:14:01,470
That was when

249
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:03,910
he executed his tricks.

250
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:14,280
After hastily finishing his act,

251
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,590
he shouted loudly,

252
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:16,520
drawing Yu San into the cabin.

253
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,520
Murder!

254
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:19,440
By the time Yu San entered the cabin,

255
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:21,080
he naturally assumed

256
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,550
that my aunt was already dead

257
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:23,960
and that the murderer

258
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:25,710
was my mother, who was holding the hairpin.

259
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:26,910
Once there

260
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:28,350
was finally someone to serve as a witness for him,

261
00:14:28,590 --> 00:14:29,880
he struck the final blow

262
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,550
and framed my mother for the crime.

263
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:33,000
This is a total lie!

264
00:14:33,150 --> 00:14:34,550
Utterly absurd!

265
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:35,960
Your Honor,

266
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,590
she is falsely accusing me!

267
00:14:45,030 --> 00:14:46,200
Ms. Ji,

268
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,400
your deductions

269
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:49,030
are certainly intriguing.

270
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:50,230
Unfortunately,

271
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:52,230
besides the bloodstains on the victim's clothes,

272
00:14:52,550 --> 00:14:54,550
there is no direct evidence

273
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:57,590
to prove that Li Feng committed the murder.

274
00:14:57,590 --> 00:15:00,150
Meanwhile, the evidence against your mother is undeniable.

275
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:03,350
I must still sentence your mother...

276
00:15:03,590 --> 00:15:04,710
Hold on, Magistrate Meng.

277
00:15:06,350 --> 00:15:07,280
Li Feng, can you guess

278
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,110
why I'm so certain

279
00:15:09,230 --> 00:15:10,520
that you are the murderer?

280
00:15:13,590 --> 00:15:14,960
I have another witness.

281
00:15:15,350 --> 00:15:17,520
He saw Li Feng commit murder with his own eyes.

282
00:15:17,790 --> 00:15:18,590
A witness?

283
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:20,910
I, humble citizen Yu San, am willing to testify!

284
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:26,960
